# Boatyard Slip — Illustration Prompt

Create a richly detailed, roughly square digital painting sized to sit beside narrative text on desktop or mobile screens. Depict a grounded late-medieval harbor campaign setting with rollers, wedges, timber cradles, pins, iron collars, and hull-side fittings. Emphasize crisp readability, brighter maritime color accents, and clear spatial separation more than muddy painterly atmosphere.

- Composition: practical slip-side work area with benches of hardware and a clear route back to the pier.
- Key elements: wedges, slip rollers, spare pins, braces, and fittings laid out for repair or departure preparation.
- Character focus: shipwright labor that looks minor until it stops an entire launch.
- Navigation hint: show the return route toward Rope Crane Pier and some visual connection toward the ship berth.

